node.text:
After moving to Oregon, Rashad Frazier (@pulledtogether) felt inspired by his outdoor experiences and a love for good food. He founded @camp.yoshi, a custom adventure program, to provide a place for the Black community and allies to reconnect with nature over good food. “We’re trying to demystify what it means to get outside for Black and Brown folks.”

Watch the short film about Rashad's journey and a recent Camp Yoshi dinner now on IGTV. Thanks to @faithevebee and @thewilderstudio for your partnership.

node.text: Using a cooler as a cutting board and her hiking boot as a wine opener, @chefmariahines proves you can make a delicious meal outside using only camp tools and a few simple ingredients. Watch to see how Maria—James Beard Award winner, Iron Chef America champion and big-wall rock climber—creates pasta from scratch at camp.

node.title: Cook Out with Chef Maria Hines: Fresh Pasta at Camp

Whether you’re a stay-at-home parent, weekend warrior, recreational enthusiast or professional athlete, we all strive to have the energy, cognitive function and vitality to fully engage in our daily lives.

node.title: Everyday Performance Foods: Food as Medicine with @chefmariahines

“As an outdoor enthusiast and chef, I’m passionate about diversifying the outdoors and the food we all choose to enjoy outdoors. I hope that by cooking on the trail, I can inspire people to get outdoors more, try new food and possibly cook a meal in the beauty of Mother Nature. Every culture experiences food unique to their culture, which is beautiful. It’s the love of food that unites us all. There’s something so magical about cooking outside surrounded by fresh mountain air and gorgeous views. It’s truly addictive!” 

–@kenapeay, #REIpartner and co-op member since 2006

node.text:
After moving to Oregon, Rashad Frazier (@pulledtogether) felt inspired by his outdoor experiences and a love for good food. He founded @camp.yoshi, a custom adventure program, to provide a place for the Black community and allies to reconnect with nature over good food. “We’re trying to demystify what it means to get outside for Black and Brown folks.”

Watch the short film about Rashad's journey and a recent Camp Yoshi dinner now on IGTV. Thanks to @faithevebee and @thewilderstudio for your partnership.

node.text: In 2019, #REIpartner Mikah Meyer (@mikahmey) set a world record when he visited all 419 U.S. national park sites in one, three-year road trip. Since then, he's used his platform to promote LGBTQIA+ inclusivity in the outdoors with @outsidesafespace. Listen to his story on the Wild Ideas Worth Living podcast at the link in our bio.

After a fall on New Year's Eve in 2018 left her paralyzed, thru hiker and #REImember Molly Schneider (@mollyaschneider21) began questioning her relationship with the outdoors: "Will I ever thru-hike again? Will I ever stand taller than the trees again?" But she says her trek taught her one very important lesson—if the trail changes, you adapt.

Read her full story at the link in our bio.
